The brand identity is "Industrial Authority." Every page must feel built, not just designed. We prioritize structural strength, high-contrast readability, and B2B reliability.
Tone: Engineering-grade, reliable, 






3. COMPONENT PATTERNS & LAYOUT RULES
A. The "500-Word Rule" (Tabbed Content System)
Any section where content exceeds 500 words MUST use the Industrial Tab System.
Structure: Horizontal icon-based navigation bar.
Logic: Toggles between Residential, Commercial, Logistics, and Compliance.
Visuals: White active state with a border-b-4 border-brand-gold. Dark inactive state.
Purpose: Prevents "Wall of Text" fatigue and improves user retention on high-authority SEO pages.
B. The Sticky Jump Menu (Scannability Anchor)
Location: Fixed to the top of the viewport (below main header).
Appearance: bg-brand-dark (Dark background), gold active-link underlining.
Interaction: Smooth-scroll to target IDs (Overview, Capabilities, Hauling, FAQ).
C. Asymmetric Layouts (The 7/12 Rule)
Formula: 7/12 width for text content, 5/12 width for visual assets.
Visual Accents: Images in these sections must have a border-b-8 border-brand-gold.
The "Light Element": Use a decorative backing frame (an empty bg-brand-light box) offset by -2rem behind images to create depth.
D. Card Blocks (Industrial Grid)
Hover State: Cards must transition from bg-white (Light) to bg-brand-dark (Dark) or vice versa.
Borders: Heavy top borders (border-t-8 border-brand-gold).
Icons: Large (w-12 h-12), stroke width 1, color brand-gold.

4. MOTION & INTERACTION DESIGN
A. Scroll Reveals (The Parallax Effect)
Hero Images: Utilize animate-slow-zoom (10% scale increase over 20s).
Typography: All headers use the RevealOnScroll hook (Fade-in + 12px Y-axis translate-up).
Staggered Delays: Child elements in a grid must use incremental delays (0ms, 150ms, 300ms).
B. Mouse Hover Dynamics
CTA Buttons:
Primary: Gold to White transition with a -1px transform translate-y on hover.
Secondary: Outlined to Solid transition.


Service Cards: Subtle scale-up (scale-105) and grayscale-to-color transition on imagery.
C. Micro-Animations
The Pulse: Every "24/7" or "Now Booking" badge must feature a pulse animation on a 2px radial dot.
Engineering Grid: Dark sections must utilize a radial-gradient background (30px grid) that stays static as the page content scrolls over it.

5. SECTION DIVIDERS & STRUCTURAL ELEMENTS
The Structural Divider: A 1px gray-200 line across the full width, with a 24px brand-gold bar at the start of the container.
Hero-to-Body Transition: Use a "Floating Card" overlay (overlapping the hero section by -64px) to bridge sections.
Contact Blocks: Always split 50/50. Left is "Emergency/Dark" (Red/Dark themes). Right is "Quote/Gold" (Gold/Light themes).

